Description of incident: Dallas County Texas has admitted to a databreach of residents information that has been accessible online for over 6 months. The information included names, addresses, Social Security numbers and birth dates of residents, including children. The county has had over 6 months to pull the data offline, however as of the time of this report by CBS the information had not yet been pulled.More information: http://www.msn.com/en-us/news/us/cbs11-investigates-north-texas-security...
